South Korea has increased its duty on crudeoil imports to 4.29 dlrs a barrel from 3.29 dlrs, effectivetoday, the energy ministry said.    The duty, to raise funds for special energy projects, wasadjusted after average crude import prices rose to 16.85 dlrs abarrel in April, from 16.65 dlrs in March and 13.08 dlrs inApril 1986, ministry officials said.    A separate 24.5 pct import tax on crude oil is unchanged. REUTER&#3;